abstract: Candidates are leaving potential Republican converts without options.
snippet: Candidates are leaving potential Republican converts without options.
lead_paragraph: Under President Trump, a small slice of America’s electorate seeks a reason to call the Democratic Party home for the very first time. But without adequate hospitality to welcome them, they will disappear quickly.

headline_main: Why Are Democrats Jilting G.O.P. Voters Who Want to Like Them?

lead_paragraph: Gail Collins: Bret, where should we start? Democratic debate? Impeachment? Mideast crisis? Rudy Giuliani? Actually, as a New Yorker I always figured that someday Rudy would do something even more outrageous than the time he called a news conference to announce he was separating from his wife before he told said spouse. But I did not imagine it would include sleazy Ukrainians and Joe Biden’s son.

abstract: We asked veterans of political debates for the advice they would give to each of the Democratic hopefuls onstage Tuesday.
snippet: We asked veterans of political debates for the advice they would give to each of the Democratic hopefuls onstage Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: As part of our 2020 debate coverage, we are asking political debate coaches and experts to tell us what each candidate needs to do to win, and what advice they would give those onstage. Then we will ask the experts afterward how the candidates did.

abstract: The Hawaii congresswoman has railed against what she sees as a “rigging” of the election by Democratic Party leaders and corporate media.
snippet: The Hawaii congresswoman has railed against what she sees as a “rigging” of the election by Democratic Party leaders and corporate media.
lead_paragraph: Representative Tulsi Gabbard, one of 12 Democratic presidential candidates who have qualified for this week’s televised debate, said on Monday that she would participate in the forum after raising the possibility of boycotting it to protest what she sees as a “rigging” of the election.

abstract: Income-driven repayment programs cover eight million borrowers, but they could be helping more if they were simpler and reached the people who needed them.
snippet: Income-driven repayment programs cover eight million borrowers, but they could be helping more if they were simpler and reached the people who needed them.
lead_paragraph: With more than 7.5 million student loan borrowers in default and nearly 2 million others seriously behind on their payments, there’s little question that the handful of federal programs designed to help struggling borrowers pay what they can afford aren’t working for everyone.

abstract: A police officer fired the shot that killed Atatiana Jefferson from outside her bedroom window. A neighbor had reported two doors ajar.
snippet: A police officer fired the shot that killed Atatiana Jefferson from outside her bedroom window. A neighbor had reported two doors ajar.
lead_paragraph: FORT WORTH — Minutes before she was shot and killed by a Fort Worth police officer, Atatiana K. Jefferson was playing video games in her bedroom with her 8-year-old nephew, a lawyer for her family said Sunday.

abstract: The Democratic presidential candidates agree on many gun control measures, like an assault weapons ban. But they’re split on other ideas, like a federal gun registry.
snippet: The Democratic presidential candidates agree on many gun control measures, like an assault weapons ban. But they’re split on other ideas, like a federal gun registry.
lead_paragraph: The 2020 Democratic presidential candidates are far more forceful and united on gun control than their predecessors, endorsing a wide range of policies that past nominees sidestepped or rejected, according to a New York Times survey of the 19 campaigns.
